  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 889faa658c7b2c94ea4fff939bf8022e, type: 3}
  m_Name: DialogNPCInfirmary
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Name: Stefano
  Icon: {fileID: -2105629146, guid: d556a7f542c7d03429c5a535ce31a084, type: 3}
  HasInteraction: 0
  interactionType: 1
  Greeting: Hey...
  Day1Dialog:
  - "You\u2019ve come to the infirmary? Good, boy. Look at this \u2014 men burned
    by cannon fire, cut by swords.\nWe dress the wounds, stop the bleeding, and pray
    the powder doesn\u2019t ignite the bandages.\nEach night, some are ferried to
    Fort St. Angelo for safety. Those who stay\u2026 we do what we can."
  Day2FirstTimeDialog:
  - "Yesterday, the ravelin fell. The wounded came flooding in \u2014 musket burns,
    arrows, splintered bones.\nSome get infections we cannot stop, even with the
    best care.\nAt night, rowers take the worst to St. Angelo \u2014 a few survive,
    some never reach the shore."
  Day2MetBeforeDialog:
  - "Yesterday was hell, boy. The ravelin taken, men mangled, bleeding.\nI patched
    eyes, arms, and backsides alike, praying they\u2019d live long enough to fight
    another day."
  Day3FirstTimeDialog:
  - "Now hear the cannon fire? Dragut has come, new guns on Gallows\u2019 Point.\nWe
    treat burns and shattered limbs, and yet the docks bring more volunteers each
    night.\nSome swim across the harbour, exhausted and cut, only to be thrown on
    our tables."
  Day3MetBeforeDialog:
  - "The hammering of Dragut\u2019s guns shakes the walls \u2014 and our infirmary.\nLast
    night we ferried a dozen more from Birgu. All with deep wounds, some infected
    already.\nWe work as fast as we can, but there are too many."
  Day4FirstTimeDialog:
  - "The walls hold, but our men suffer. Arrows, musket burns, cannon shrapnel \u2014
    the list grows.\nWe fight infections with herbs, clean dressings, and prayers.\nSome
    are carried nightly to St. Angelo. Some never make it.\nThe fort\u2019s survival
    depends on every living Knight, but the cost is terrible."
  Day4MetBeforeDialog:
  - "Another day of terror, boy. I\u2019ve patched what I could. Some men live, some
    die on my table.\nEvery night the strong are ferried across \u2014 the weak\u2026
    left here.\nI work faster than the deaths arrive, but it\u2019s never enough."
  Day5FirstTimeDialog:
  - Tomorrow may be the bloodiest day. Every repair, ration, and plank is survival
    against overwhelming odds. The fort will be tested like never before, but its
    foundations hold firm.
  Day5MetBeforeDialog:
  - "This is it. Every repair, ration, reinforced gate may decide who lives. The
    fort may hold, but suffering is immense. Courage here comes at a terrible price
    \u2014 remember that, boy."
  dayNumber: 1
  metOnday1: 0
  metOnday2: 0
  metOnday3: 0
  metOnday4: 0
  metOnday5: 0
